The paper discusses a machine learning paradigm designed to address non-stationary environments with non-exhaustive training sets, which is a common problem in many real-world applications. The paper proposes a Bayesian nonparametric approach to address this problem, which is a popular research area in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
